intro: Acer platanoides f. schwedleri, commonly known as the Swedish maple, is a cultivar of the Norway maple. It is characterized by its large, palmate leaves that are typically lobed and have a distinctive white or cream-colored margin. The plant produces small, greenish-yellow flowers in early spring, followed by winged samaras that disperse its seeds. It is a deciduous tree or shrub that thrives in temperate climates and prefers moist, well-drained soils. This cultivar is often used in landscaping for its ornamental value and hardy nature.
